\title{bootabc: Bootstrap Experiment Confidence Intervals}
\description{
Computes bootstrap confidence intervals for key performance indicators (KPIs) measured in online controlled experiments (A/B tests), where data is aggregated to one row per customer or visitor. Supports compound KPIs defined as ratios of sums, such as spend per active day, and comparisons between experiment variants. Resampling runs through a streaming 'C++' kernel so that large experiments remain tractable. Variance can be reduced using pre-experiment data via the CUPED method of Deng, Xu, Kohavi and Walker (2013) \doi{10.1145/2433396.2433413}.
